---
import '../styles/tokens.css';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Why this exists. | OurOrigin</title>
    
    <meta name="description" content="OurOrigin exists because the people and places behind real products deserve to be seen, not kept in the background of a marketing story.">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://ourorigin.in/why">
    <meta property="og:title" content="Why this exists. | OurOrigin">
    <meta property="og:description" content="A small business sourcing from the Western Ghats. We show you the origin and let you reach your own conclusions.">
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://ourorigin.in/why">
    <meta property="og:image" content="https://ourorigin.in/og-image.jpg">

    <!-- Google Fonts with display=swap as explicitly requested -->
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400..900&family=Cormorant+Garamond:wght@300;400;500&family=DM+Mono:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body, html {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: var(--color-forest-deep);
            color: var(--color-warm-cream);
            height: 100%;
        }
        .page-container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20vh 5vw;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 2rem;
        }
        h1 {
            font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
            font-weight: 400;
        }
        p {
            font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
            opacity: 0.9;
        }
        .nav-link {
            font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
            color: var(--color-warm-cream);
            text-decoration: none;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            margin-top: 4rem;
            display: inline-block;
            border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(244, 241, 235, 0.3);
            padding-bottom: 0.2rem;
            transition: border-color 0.3s ease;
            align-self: flex-start;
        }
        .nav-link:hover {
            border-bottom-color: var(--color-warm-cream);
        }
        .fssai-footer {
            margin-top: auto;
            padding-top: 4rem;
            font-family: 'DM Mono', monospace;
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--color-warm-cream);
            opacity: 0.4;
            text-align: left;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <GlobalNav />
    <main id="main-content" class="page-container">
        <h1>Why this exists.</h1>
        
        <p>Most products arrive with a label. A label says what something is. It rarely says where — not really. Not the place, the soil, the season, the person. Not the thing behind the thing. OurOrigin exists because we believe those hidden layers are the most interesting part. And because we think the people and places behind real products deserve to be seen, not kept in the background of a marketing story.</p>
        
        <p>We source from the Western Ghats — the forests, hills, and homesteads of Kerala and Tamil Nadu. Five origins, different in altitude and character, connected by the same ridge of forest running down the spine of peninsular India. Each product we sell is traceable to a place we can name, a community we can describe, and a method we can document. We don't make claims about sustainability or ethics or purity. We show you the origin and let you reach your own conclusions.</p>
        
        <p>We are a small business. We don't have a warehouse. We pack and ship directly. When you buy from us, you talk to us directly — via WhatsApp, the way a person talks to a person. That's not a feature. It's just how this works when you haven't automated the part that shouldn't be automated.</p>
        
        <p style="font-family: 'Cinzel', serif; font-size: 1rem; color: var(--color-gold); margin-top: 1rem;">From the Source.</p>
        
        <a href="/" class="nav-link">Return to the Matrix</a>
        
        <div class="fssai-footer">FSSAI Reg. No. 21326135000354</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
